attributes.description: Juicy sausages. Creamy mash. Onion marmalade? Not your regular trio, we know. It’s onion marmalade that gives your gravy a rich tang, bringing this British comfort classic to life. Crisp green beans and oven-roasted carrots make it bursting with goodness too!
attributes.name: Extra Special Bangers 'N’ Mash

attributes.description: This hearty courgette pasta doesn't just have a rich tomato sauce, it's layered with mozzarella, cheddar and Italian hard cheese for a tasty and wholesome midweek bake.
attributes.name: 3 Cheese Veg-Packed Pasta Bake

attributes.description: "Who doesn't love a bit of sweet chilli? Here's my secret recipe for unbelievable chicken, served up with rice that I've packed with peas, carrots and black sesame seeds. Boom!"
attributes.name: Sweet Chilli Chicken With Veg Packed Rice

claims.disclaimer: Carb refuel recipes are substantial meals, full of carbs and protein, perfect post-workout to refuel your muscles.

attributes.description: For these Indian-inspired burritos, you'll stuff tortillas with curried chicken, crisp lettuce and sweet pilau rice. Finish with mango and nigella seed yoghurt, and serve. Now that's a wrap!
attributes.name: Chicken Shashlik Burritos With Mango Yoghurt

attributes.description: Whether it’s fresh out the oven or tomorrow’s lunch, lasagne is always a firm family favourite. You'll add a splash of Henderson’s Relish to this comfort food classic for a flavourful Gousto twist!
attributes.name: Big Flavour Lean Beef Lasagne

attributes.description: "I love a DIY spice blend, and this Mexican one goes perfectly with pork! The flavours are banging with a chunky chopped salad, and to top it off it's low carb too. What a winner!"
attributes.name: Mexican Spiced Pork Steak & Kidney Bean Salad

claims.disclaimer: Reduced carb recipes don't contain any starchy carbohydrates like bread, pasta or rice. You'll get energy from fats and protein instead.

attributes.description: This wholesome tagine is filled with chickpeas and butternut squash, which you'll simmer in a punchy harissa and baharat sauce, and sweeten with dried apricots. Serve with minty couscous.
attributes.name: Chickpea, Butternut Squash & Apricot Tagine

attributes.description: Whether it's fresh out the oven or tomorrow's lunch, lasagne is always a firm family favourite. We've used meat-free mince in this one, so vegetarians can enjoy it too!
attributes.name: Big Flavour Meat-Free Lasagne

attributes.description: Grab 10 minutes, and treat yourself to this succulent king prawn spaghetti tossed in a punchy tomato and garlic sauce. Sizzle, toss, done!
attributes.name: Chilli, Garlic & Jumbo Prawn Spaghetti

labels.for4: 1 truffle flavoured extra virgin olive oil sachet (8ml)

attributes.description: Get ready for rich, mushroomy flavour in minutes. You'll cook baby button and chestnut mushrooms with spinach and soya cream, before adding curly amorini pasta. Top with chives, toasted pine nuts and truffle oil to serve.
attributes.name: Plant-Based Creamy Truffle Mushroom Amorini

attributes.description: A classic pathia is sweet and tangy, with a slight kick from the fragrant spices. Serve this basa version with turmeric and cumin-infused rice, and buttery garlic & coriander naans. Curry night, sorted!
attributes.name: Basa Pathia, Turmeric Rice & Naan

attributes.description: Stir-fries don’t get much better than this. In 10 minutes, you'll serve up sweet chilli turkey mince with egg noodles and zingy lime. Garnish with spring onion and peanuts for crunch, and it's done!
attributes.name: Sweet Chilli Turkey Noodles

attributes.description: Set the table first, because these noodles are ready in a flash! You'll pan-fry lean beef mince and mangetout in a chilli jam sauce, then serve over sesame noodles. Sizzle, toss, done!
attributes.name: Lean Sticky Ginger Beef Noodles

attributes.description: This warming casserole from Normandy combines chicken, apples and wholegrain mustard in a rich, creamy stew. Serve with crisp green beans and crusty ciabatta to mop up the delicious sauce.

images.description: Let the oven do the hard work, for a meal full of rich, slow-cooked flavour.
images.title: Prepped in 5

images.description: Pour yourself a glass while your chicken thighs cook in creme fraiche, apples and mustard.
images.title: For sheer indulgence

attributes.name: Oven-Baked Normandy Chicken & Apple Casserole

attributes.description: Sizzle up a spicy Middle Eastern-style stew, with golden halloumi and baby leaf spinach simmered in a rich tomato sauce. This one's ready in 10 mins, and served with sultana couscous on the side.
attributes.name: Spicy Halloumi Stew With Couscous

attributes.description: Escape to Thailand in minutes with our fastest pad thai yet. You'll pack noodles with chicken and a rainbow of pre-chopped veg, before adding a zingy tamarind sauce. Top with peanuts and coriander to serve.

images.description: With the prep sorted, whip up healthy and delicious meals in a flash.
images.title: All Chopped

images.description: Heat up the hob and stir up Thai rice noodles and rainbow veggies. No chopping board needed.

attributes.name: Chicken Pad Thai With Rainbow Veg

attributes.description: Our twist on fish pie is so simple to prepare. You'll cook smoked fish in a creamy mustard and spinach sauce, top with crushed potatoes and bake it until golden and bubbling.
attributes.name: Simple Smoked Fish Florentine Bake

attributes.description: Brilliant for weeknights and slurp-tastic for adults and children alike. Rustle up a simply perfect lean spag bol with a rich meaty sauce topped with lashings of melty cheddar and fresh basil. Dinner is served!
